public enum CLICommand extends Enum<CLICommand>
Enum that contains the types of commands available to players in the Command Line Interface.

  • Constructor Details

    • CLICommand

      private CLICommand(boolean isGameCommand, String command, String arguments, String description)
      Creates a new command for players to use in the Command Line Interface. This constructor defaults to the command having no aliases.
      Parameters:
      isGameCommand - Whether the command is game-specific or relative so some other functionality (e.g. the chat).
      command - The command string.
      arguments - The arguments for the command. This is only used to print the usage of this command.
      description - A description of what the command does.

    • CLICommand

      private CLICommand(boolean isGameCommand, String command, String arguments, String description, Set<String> aliases)
      Creates a new command for players to use in the Command Line Interface.
      Parameters:
      isGameCommand - Whether the command is game-specific or relative to some other functionality (e.g. the chat).
      command - The command string.
      arguments - The arguments for the command. This is only used to print the usage of this command.
      description - A description of what the command does.
      aliases - A set of aliases for this command. An alias is an alternative way of spelling the command (e.g. color and colour are both valid).

    • matches

      public boolean matches(String input)
      Checks whether an input matches this command or one of its aliases.
      Parameters:
      input - The user's input.
      Returns:
      true if the input matches this command or any of its aliases, false otherwise. Note that a command matches even if it's partially spelled (e.g. "a" matches "games"). It is up to the caller to check that this is the command the user actually meant to execute.

    • exactMatch

      public boolean exactMatch(String input)
      Checks whether an input matches exactly this command (does not count aliases).
      Parameters:
      input - The user's input.
      Returns:
      true if the input exactly matches this command, false otherwise.
